	(1, 2, 'agent', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-09 20:30:11', 'The term "cognitive computing" refers to systems that learn at scale, reason with purpose, and interact with humans naturally. These systems are designed to mimic the human brain\'s ability to learn, understand, and make decisions. They are capable of processing vast amounts of complex information, identifying patterns, and making predictions based on that data. Cognitive computing is often used in areas such as artificial intelligence, machine learning, natural language processing, and robotics.', 'gpt-4', '1'),
	(2, 1, 'agent', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-09 20:30:31', 'A business plan is a formal written document that outlines the goals, objectives, and strategies of a business. It serves as a roadmap for the business, detailing the steps necessary to achieve its goals. It also provides a way to measure progress and make necessary adjustments. A business plan typically includes the following sections:\n\n1. Executive Summary: This is a brief overview of the business, its mission, and its unique selling proposition.\n\n2. Company Description: This section provides detailed information about the business, including its legal structure, location, and the product or service it offers.\n\n3. Market Analysis: This section provides an overview of the industry, including trends, target market, and competition.\n\n4. Organization and Management: This section outlines the organizational structure of the business and the qualifications of the management team.\n\n5. Service or Product Line: This section describes the product or service the business offers, including its benefits and lifecycle.\n\n6. Marketing and Sales Strategy: This section outlines the business\'s marketing and sales strategy, including pricing, promotion, and distribution.\n\n7. Funding Request: If the business plan is being used to secure funding, this section outlines the funding request and how the funds will be used.\n\n8. Financial Projections: This section provides a forecast of the business\'s financial performance, including income statements, cash flow statements, and balance sheets.\n\n9. Appendix: This section includes any additional documents or information that support the business plan, such as resumes, permits, or contracts.', 'gpt-4', '1'),
	(3, 1, 'agent', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-09 20:48:26', 'The term "emotional intelligence" refers to the ability to identify, understand, and manage emotions in a positive way. This includes the ability to recognize your own emotions and those of others, to understand the effect of these emotions, and to use this information to guide your thinking and behavior. Emotional intelligence can affect various aspects of your life, such as your behavior and relationships. It can also help you to manage stress and deal with challenges effectively.', 'gpt-4', '1'),
	(4, 2, 'agent', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-09 20:48:41', 'The term "AI" stands for Artificial Intelligence. It refers to the simulation of human intelligence in machines that are programmed to think like humans and mimic their actions. The term may also be applied to any machine that exhibits traits associated with a human mind such as learning and problem-solving.', 'gpt-4', '1');

